fields.name: dx
fields.description: X axis shift at the origin (accepted range is +/- 5000.0 meters).

fields.name: dy
fields.description: Y axis shift at the origin (accepted range is +/- 5000.0 meters).

fields.name: dz
fields.description: Z axis shift at the origin (accepted range is +/- 5000.0 meters).

fields.name: rotX
fields.description: Rotation about the X axis (accepted range is +/- 20.0 milli-arc seconds).

fields.name: rotY
fields.description: Rotation about the Y axis (accepted range is +/- 20.0 milli-arc seconds).

fields.name: rotZ
fields.description: Rotation about the Z axis (accepted range is +/- 20.0 milli-arc seconds).

fields.name: scale
fields.description: Scale change (accepted range is 0.0 to 50.0 parts per million).

issues: Inconsistent field capitalization (rotx, roty vs rotX, rotY)
Inconsistent field capitalization (rotx, roty vs rotX, rotY)
Inconsistent field capitalization (maja vs majA, rotx/roty/rotz vs rotX/rotY/rotZ)

adjudication.reasoning: The binary structure of UBX-CFG-DAT (Set) is consistent across all analyzed receiver generations (M8, M9, F9). It consists of a 44-byte payload with identical data types and offsets. The canonical structure is derived from the majority of the F9 sources and the M8 source, which consistently use the field names `majA`, `rotX`, `rotY`, and `rotZ` and the unit 's' (seconds). Extractions 1, 2, and 6 are technically valid regarding the data structure but contain inconsistencies in field name capitalization (e.g., 'rotx', 'maja') and units ('S') which deviate from the standard protocol definition found in the other five sources.
